com.github.hotware.lucene.extension.bean.type

Class StockType

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.hotware.lucene.extension.bean.type.StockType

  • public final class StockType
extends Object
    Inner classes of this type contain basic Types that are shipped with the extension. Most of the time these types are sufficient

    All Numbers have two different types:
    One [Number]Type and one [Number]StringType.
    The first one tells Lucene to store the Field in a Numeric Field (with the corresponding Lucene NumericType) and the second one converts the Number into a String and then stores that String into the Document.

    In fact, all Types that don't have a specific name (i.e. SerializeType) convert the field by toString() into the Document and retrieve the value
    Author:
    Martin Braun
